It is believed that the men originated from neighbouring Lesotho, Zimbabwe and Mozambique. JOHANNESBURG Search and recovery operations at a disused mine shaft in Welkom are expected to continue on Friday where the bodies of 29 illegal miners have so far been found.The men died in a gas explosion earlier this week.It is believed that the men originated from neighbouring Lesotho, Zimbabwe and Mozambique.The police's Thandi Mbambo said: We are also continuing with our investigations and two families have come forward to identify bodies and took them back to their respective countries. 